                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d700">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">660f.116Auto/22: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Czechoslovakia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gittings</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Prague</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-03-20T17:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 20, 1928—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 20—1:05 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>21. Department’s No. 9, March 15, 5 p.m. It now appears that information was
                    premature because no licenses actually granted yet. I am requesting expedition
                    and will promptly inform Department. Full report by mail.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gittings</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
